      "content": "thats a good high level view. but i'm seeing a lot of news lately talking about how \"existential risk\" is actually just a distraction or even a way for big companies to pull up the ladder behind them. do you think the \"existential risk\" argument is actually a mainstream scientific concern or is it more of a speculative thing used to push certain policies?",
